In a bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar and flour. Whisk in sour cream and vanilla. Arrange raspberries evenly in the pie shell. Spread sour cream mixture over berries. Combine bread crumbs, 2 teaspoons sugar, and melted butter or margarine. Sprinkle over pie. Bake at 400 degrees F (205 degrees C) for 30 to 40 minutes, or until pastry and filling are golden. Cool on rack. Serve same day at room temperature.